Text.Value: *The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
Take a deep breath - and attack.
This ain't your town, friend. But it can be your grave.
Aye, now that's a beat! Needs drumming, though - got some skulls inside you could use. Go on.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bopping his head, appreciating your music. Friendly pointer towards the end.

Text.Value: *Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
...A True Soul. Right. Ah - welcome to Bogrot!
How about a donation instead? Some coin for the town. ([463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
ROAR.
You get nothing.
You do not give orders to me.
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
Well that's just bloody rude.
*As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
Go wake him up - and tell 'im I sent ya.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost rubbing his hands in glee

Text.Value: 'Bogrot'?
And you'll let me pass?
Go on - more of us inside.
Temper on you, eh? Fine - keep yer goods. Our crowd own this town - we can take you any time we want.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spooked by us but trying to save face

Text.Value: Then my search is over - I'm actually here to write the Ballad of Bogrot.
Or whatever you want to call it - 's your town now. Heh.
'Allo and welcome to Bogrot! Now, kindly - giz all your stuff.

EditorData.NodeContext: A goblin's closest approximation of courtesty, faintly mocking. He's loudly welcoming you to the town he has dubbed 'Bogrot'

Text.Value: I'm lookin' - just ain't seeing much. Might be we need to carve you open?
It's a fine day, my friend. Why spoil it with killing?
Blegh. Reckon you'll make sweeter sounds once we slice you a bit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not enjoying our music at all, moving to attack as much out of disgust as anything.

Text.Value: Killing you would make my day, but I don't fancy cleaning up your guts afterwards. Hand over your stuff - now.
So now it's Bogrot. And you got to give over your goods.
I'll give you another chance. Look at me again and choose your words carefully.
Nice town. I'll wipe my feet on your corpse before entering.
'Bogrot, fair Bogrot - with hills as green as goblin snot.'
It's not ready - I need to see the town first.
Hah! Nah. But it'll save us scrubbing the goo off your goods when we kill ya, see?
Ah. Right. Might be I was a little rude. All drow're welcome in Bogrot.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gulping nervously, sees we're a race that typically dominates and enslaves his.

Text.Value: Well ain't you got a sunny disposition? The bugbear'll hate ya.
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
Hah! You got guts. Now show me what colour they are.
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
I'll give you another chance. Look at me again and choose your words carefully.
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*
'Built on BONES of goblin FOE, Bogrot bears a FEAST for CROWS!'
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Bit flowersome, but you got something there. Go on in - reckon you can polish it up some once you've seen the place.

EditorData.NodeContext: Considering, cautiously critical but deeming our music not bad.

Text.Value: You what? Go on then, we're bored - give us a taste.
...Aye. Aye, I reckon that'll do nicely. The good folk of Bogrot give ya thanks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mulling it over - he was going to kill us but we've just handed him a sizable sum so he's decided to be magnanimous

Text.Value: You do not give orders to me.
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
Local soil-scratchers probably called it something else, but they's dead a hundred years.
The only thing you're getting is a beating.
How about a donation...? ([01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
Compromise, then. We'll pop your eyes out and give them the tour, eh?

Synopsis: This goblin is guarding the entrance to a town his squad have occupied. The residents are long-dead, the town abandoned, and so he's taken it upon himself to rechristen the village as 'Bogrot'.
